Use upb's portable varint path on aarch64-windows.

protobuf's upb/wire/encode.c has an AArch64 inline-asm fast path for varint
encoding (encode_longvarint), gated by UPB_ARM64_ASM. On aarch64-w64-mingw32
(llvm-mingw/clang) that macro is enabled, but LLVM cannot generate Windows SEH
unwind info for a function containing inline asm:

  fatal error: error in backend: Failed to evaluate function length in SEH unwind info

Exclude _WIN32 from UPB_ARM64_ASM so aarch64-windows uses the portable C
implementation. The asm fast path stays on aarch64 linux/android/macos/bsd.
--- a/src/protobuf/upb/port/def.inc
+++ b/src/protobuf/upb/port/def.inc
@@ -392,7 +392,9 @@
 #define UPB_PRESERVE_NONE
 #endif

-#if defined(__aarch64__) && (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__))
+// aarch64-mingw: LLVM cannot emit SEH unwind info for encode.c inline asm, so
+// use the portable C path on Windows (keeps the asm on linux/android/macos/bsd).
+#if defined(__aarch64__) && (defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)) && !defined(_WIN32)
 #define UPB_ARM64_ASM 1
 #else
 #define UPB_ARM64_ASM 0
